Alex Mitchley  Bethal – Two people were killed in Bethal, Mpumalanga on Friday evening when their car split into two after colliding with a bakkie. "Two occupants from the light motor vehicle were found on the scene with fatal injuries," said ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak.  "There was nothing that paramedics could do for them and they were declared dead on scene." One survivor from the car as well as occupants from the bakkie were treated on scene and transported to a nearby hospital for further care.   Car splits into two during a collision in Bethal, killing two people. (Pic supplied)   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  